data-triple-N3.o: "The Isle of Wight /al ov wat/ is a county and the largest island of England, located in the English Channel, on average about 35miles (5-7 km) off the coast of Hampshire, separated from Great Britain (referred to by its inhabitants as "the mainland") by a strait called the Solent. It has the distinction of being England's smallest county - but for only half of the time. It has been calculated that during high tide Wight's area is slightly less than that of Rutland, but not during low tide."@en
